<item>
            <title>[LU-19028] Fixing the squash value in the nodemap configuration.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19028</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps to reproduce the problem:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
1. Configure a nodemap (noRootSquash) on MGS with:&lt;br/&gt;
trusted=1&lt;br/&gt;
admin=1&lt;br/&gt;
squash_uid=0&lt;br/&gt;
squash_gid=0&lt;br/&gt;
Client NIDs correctly added to the nodemap ranges.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Mount the Lustre filesystem on a client listed in the nodemap range.&lt;br/&gt;
3. As root user (uid=0) on the client, attempt to:&lt;br/&gt;
touch a new file on the Lustre mount.&lt;br/&gt;
mkdir a new directory under the mount.&lt;br/&gt;
ls or chown inside existing user-owned directories.&lt;br/&gt;
4. Result:&lt;br/&gt;
Permission Denied errors are observed.&lt;br/&gt;
Root user cannot create files or directories on Lustre, despite nodemap settings intended to disable root squash.&lt;br/&gt;
5. Filesystem remounts have been attempted &#8212; no change.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
